Writescript.js
// Storage key for training requests
const STORAGE_KEY = 'trainingRequests';
const ADMIN_EMAIL = 'rykersolovey@gmail.com';

// DOM Elements
const trainingForm = document.getElementById('trainingForm');
const emailInput = document.getElementById('email');
const discordInput = document.getElementById('discord');
const requestInput = document.getElementById('request');
const adminBtn = document.getElementById('adminBtn');
const formContainer = document.getElementById('formContainer');
const adminContainer = document.getElementById('adminContainer');
const requestsList = document.getElementById('requestsList');
const closeAdminBtn = document.getElementById('closeAdminBtn');
const toast = document.getElementById('toast');

// Initialize app
function init() {
    loadEventListeners();
    checkAdminStatus();
}

// Load all event listeners
function loadEventListeners() {
    trainingForm.addEventListener('submit', handleFormSubmit);
    emailInput.addEventListener('input', checkAdminStatus);
    adminBtn.addEventListener('click', showAdminView);
    closeAdminBtn.addEventListener('click', hideAdminView);
}

// Handle form submission
function handleFormSubmit(e) {
    e.preventDefault();

    const email = emailInput.value.trim();
    const discord = discordInput.value.trim();
    const requestText = requestInput.value.trim();

    if (!email || !discord || !requestText) {
        showToast('Please fill in all fields', false);
        return;
    }

    // Create request object
    const request = {
        id: Date.now(),
        email,
        discord,
        request: requestText,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
    };

    // Save to storage
    saveRequest(request);

    // Show success toast
    showToast('Request Submitted Successfully!', true);

    // Clear form
    trainingForm.reset();

    // If admin, update admin view if visible
    if (!adminContainer.classList.contains('hidden')) {
        displayRequests();
    }
}

// Save request to localStorage
function saveRequest(request) {
    let requests = getRequests();
    requests.push(request);
    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(requests));
}

// Get all requests from localStorage
function getRequests() {
    const requests = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
    return requests ? JSON.parse(requests) : [];
}

// Check if current email is admin
function checkAdminStatus() {
    const email = emailInput.value.trim();
    if (email === ADMIN_EMAIL) {
        adminBtn.classList.remove('hidden');
    } else {
        adminBtn.classList.add('hidden');
    }
}

// Show admin view
function showAdminView() {
    formContainer.classList.add('hidden');
    adminContainer.classList.remove('hidden');
    displayRequests();
}

// Hide admin view
function hideAdminView() {
    adminContainer.classList.add('hidden');
    formContainer.classList.remove('hidden');
}

// Display all requests in admin view
function displayRequests() {
    const requests = getRequests();
    requestsList.innerHTML = '';

    if (requests.length === 0) {
        requestsList.innerHTML = `
            <div class="empty-state">
                <p>No training requests yet</p>
            </div>
        `;
        return;
    }

    // Sort by timestamp (newest first)
    requests.sort((a, b) => new Date(b.timestamp) - new Date(a.timestamp));

    requests.forEach((request, index) => {
        const card = createRequestCard(request, index);
        requestsList.appendChild(card);
    });
}

// Create request card element
function createRequestCard(request, index) {
    const card = document.createElement('div');
    card.className = 'request-card';
    card.style.animationDelay = `${index * 0.05}s`;

    const date = new Date(request.timestamp);
    const formattedDate = date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
        month: 'short',
        day: 'numeric',
        year: 'numeric',
        hour: '2-digit',
        minute: '2-digit'
    });

    card.innerHTML = `
        <div class="request-email">${escapeHtml(request.email)} ‚Ä¢ ${formattedDate}</div>
        <div class="request-discord">${escapeHtml(request.discord)}</div>
        <div class="request-text">${escapeHtml(request.request)}</div>
    `;

    return card;
}

// Show toast notification
function showToast(message, isSuccess) {
    const toastTitle = document.querySelector('.toast-title');
    const toastMessage = document.querySelector('.toast-message');
    const toastIcon = document.querySelector('.toast-icon');

    toastTitle.textContent = isSuccess ? 'Success!' : 'Error';
    toastMessage.textContent = message;
    toastIcon.textContent = isSuccess ? '‚úì' : '‚úï';

    toast.classList.add('show');

    setTimeout(() => {
        toast.classList.remove('show');
    }, 3000);
}

// Escape HTML to prevent XSS
function escapeHtml(text) {
    const div = document.createElement('div');
    div.textContent = text;
    return div.innerHTML;
}

// Add smooth input animations
function addInputAnimations() {
    const inputs = document.querySelectorAll('.input-field, .textarea-field');

    inputs.forEach(input => {
        input.addEventListener('focus', function() {
            this.parentElement.style.transform = 'translateY(-2px)';
        });

        input.addEventListener('blur', function() {
            this.parentElement.style.transform = 'translateY(0)';
        });
    });
}

// Initialize on DOM load
if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', init);
} else {
    init();
}

// Add input animations
addInputAnimations();

// Initialize particles canvas
const canvas = document.getElementById('particlesCanvas');
const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
let particles = [];

function initCanvas() {
    canvas.width = window.innerWidth;
    canvas.height = window.innerHeight;
}

class Particle {
    constructor() {
        this.x = Math.random() * canvas.width;
        this.y = Math.random() * canvas.height;
        this.size = Math.random() * 2 + 0.5;
        this.speedX = Math.random() * 0.5 - 0.25;
        this.speedY = Math.random() * 0.5 - 0.25;
        this.opacity = Math.random() * 0.5 + 0.2;
    }

    update() {
        this.x += this.speedX;
        this.y += this.speedY;

        if (this.x > canvas.width) this.x = 0;
        if (this.x < 0) this.x = canvas.width;
        if (this.y > canvas.height) this.y = 0;
        if (this.y < 0) this.y = canvas.height;
    }

    draw() {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(255, 59, 59, ${this.opacity})`;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(this.x, this.y, this.size, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx.fill();
    }
}

function createParticles() {
    particles = [];
    const particleCount = Math.min(100, Math.floor((canvas.width * canvas.height) / 15000));
    for (let i = 0; i < particleCount; i++) {
        particles.push(new Particle());
    }
}

function animateParticles() {
    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
    
    particles.forEach(particle => {
        particle.update();
        particle.draw();
    });

    // Draw ***s
    particles.forEach((p1, i) => {
        particles.slice(i + 1).forEach(p2 => {
            const dx = p1.x - p2.x;
            const dy = p1.y - p2.y;
            const distance = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);

            if (distance < 120) {
                ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(255, 59, 59, ${0.15 * (1 - distance / 120)})`;
                ctx.lineWidth = 0.5;
                ctx.beginPath();
                ctx.moveTo(p1.x, p1.y);
                ctx.lineTo(p2.x, p2.y);
                ctx.stroke();
            }
        });
    });

    requestAnimationFrame(animateParticles);
}

// Initialize app

function handleEmailInput() {

// Discord input validation

// Request input with character counter
function handleRequestInput() {
    const text = requestInput.value;
    const count = text.length;
    const max = 500;
    
    charCounter.textContent = `${count} / ${max}`;
    
    if (count > max) {
        requestInput.value = text.substring(0, max);
        charCounter.textContent = `${max} / ${max}`;
        charCounter.style.color = '#ff3b3b';
    } else if (count > max * 0.9) {
        charCounter.style.color = '#ffaa00';
    } else {
        charCounter.style.color = '#707070';
    }
}

// Handle form submission
function handleFormSubmit(e) {
    e.preventDefault();

    const email = emailInput.value.trim();
    const discord = discordInput.value.trim();
    const requestText = requestInput.value.trim();

    // Validate
    if (!email || !discord || !requestText) {
        showToast('Please fill in all fields', false);
        return;
    }

    if (!/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/.test(email)) {
        showToast('Please enter a valid email', false);
        return;
    }

    // Create request object
    const request = {
        id: Date.now(),
        email,
        discord,
        request: requestText,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
    };

    // Save to storage
    saveRequest(request);

    // Show success toast
    showToast('Request Submitted Successfully!', true);

    // Clear form
    trainingForm.reset();
    document.getElementById('emailStatus').className = 'input-status';
    document.getElementById('discordStatus').className = 'input-status';
    charCounter.textContent = '0 / 500';
    charCounter.style.color = '#707070';

    // Update total requests counter
    updateTotalRequests();

    // If admin, update admin view if visible
    if (!adminContainer.classList.contains('hidden')) {
        displayRequests();
    }
}

// Save request to localStorage
function saveRequest(request) {
    let requests = getRequests();
    requests.push(request);
    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(requests));
}

// Get all requests from localStorage
function getRequests() {
    const requests = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
    return requests ? JSON.parse(requests) : [];
}

// Delete request
function deleteRequest(id) {
    let requests = getRequests();
    requests = requests.filter(r => r.id !== id);
    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(requests));
    updateTotalRequests();
    displayRequests();
}

// Update total requests counter
function updateTotalRequests() {
    const count = getRequests().length;
    totalRequestsEl.textContent = count;
    if (requestCountEl) {
        requestCountEl.textContent = `${count} Request${count !== 1 ? 's' : ''}`;
    }
}

        adminBtn.classList.remove('hidden');

        adminBtn.classList.add('hidden');
    }
}

    displayRequests();

// Filter requests by date
function filterByDate(requests, filter) {
    if (filter === 'all') return requests;
    
    const now = new Date();
    const today = new Date(now.getFullYear(), now.getMonth(), now.getDate());
    const weekAgo = new Date(today.getTime() - 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
    
    return requests.filter(request => {
        const requestDate = new Date(request.timestamp);
        if (filter === 'today') {
            return requestDate >= today;
        } else if (filter === 'week') {
            return requestDate >= weekAgo;
        }
        return true;
    });
}

// Display all requests in admin view
function displayRequests() {
    let requests = getRequests();
    
    // Apply date filter
    requests = filterByDate(requests, currentFilter);
    
    // Apply search filter
    const searchTerm = searchInput.value.toLowerCase();
    if (searchTerm) {
        requests = requests.filter(r => 
            r.email.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm) ||
            r.discord.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm) ||
            r.request.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm)
        );
    }
    
    requestsList.innerHTML = '';

    if (requests.length === 0) {
        requestsList.innerHTML = `
            <div class="empty-state">
                <p>${searchTerm ? 'No matching requests found' : 'No training requests yet'}</p>
            </div>
        `;
        return;
    }

    // Sort by timestamp (newest first)
    requests.sort((a, b) => new Date(b.timestamp) - new Date(a.timestamp));

    requests.forEach((request, index) => {
        const card = createRequestCard(request, index);
        requestsList.appendChild(card);
    });
}

// Create request card element
function createRequestCard(request, index) {
    const card = document.createElement('div');
    card.className = 'request-card';
    card.style.animationDelay = `${index * 0.05}s`;

    const date = new Date(request.timestamp);
    const formattedDate = date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
        month: 'short',
        day: 'numeric',
        year: 'numeric',
        hour: '2-digit',
        minute: '2-digit'
    });

    card.innerHTML = `
        <div class="request-header">
            <div class="request-meta">
                <div class="request-email">${escapeHtml(request.email)}</div>
                <div class="request-discord">${escapeHtml(request.discord)}</div>
                <div class="request-date">${formattedDate}</div>
            </div>
            <div class="request-actions">
                <button class="action-btn" onclick="deleteRequestPrompt(${request.id})" title="Delete">üóëÔ∏è</button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="request-text">${escapeHtml(request.request)}</div>
    `;

    return card;
}

// Hide toast
function hideToast() {
    toast.classList.remove('show');
    setTimeout(() => {
        toast.classList.add('hidden');
    }, 300);
}

// Escape HTML to prevent XSS
function escapeHtml(text) {
    const div = document.createElement('div');
    div.textContent = text;
    return div.innerHTML;
}

// Add smooth input animations
function addInputAnimations() {
    const inputs = document.querySelectorAll('.input-field, .textarea-field');

    inputs.forEach(input => {
        input.addEventListener('focus', function() {
            this.parentElement.style.transform = 'translateY(-2px)';
        });

        input.addEventListener('blur', function() {
            this.parentElement.style.transform = 'translateY(0)';
        });
    });
}

Perfect choice! Here's how to set up rivals-training.js.org:

üöÄ Setup rivals-training.js.org (FREE)

Step 1: Create a GitHub Account (if you don't have one)

  1. Go to: https://github.com/join
  2. Sign up (free)
  3. Verify your email

Step 2: Upload Your Files to GitHub

  1. Create a new repository:

    • Go to: https://github.com/new
    • Name it: rivals-training
    • Make it Public
    • Click "Create repository"

  2. Upload your files:

    • Click "uploading an existing file"
    • Drag and drop these files:
      • index.html
      • styles.css
      • script.js
      • netlify.toml (optional)
    • Click "Commit changes"

Step 3: Enable GitHub Pages

  1. In your repository, click Settings (top right)
  2. Scroll down to Pages (left sidebar)
  3. Under "Source", select main branch
  4. Click Save
  5. Your site is now live at: yourusername.github.io/rivals-training

Step 4: Get rivals-training.js.org

  1. Fork the js.org repository:

    • Go to: https://github.com/js-org/js.org
    • Click Fork (top right)

  2. Edit the domains file:

    • In YOUR forked repo, go to cnames_active.js
    • Click the pencil icon (Edit)
    • Add this line (alphabetically):
    javascript
    "rivals-training": "yourusername.github.io/rivals-training",
    • Replace yourusername with your actual GitHub username

  3. Create Pull Request:

    • Scroll down, click "Commit changes"
    • Click "Pull request"
    • Click "Create pull request"
    • Add title: "Add rivals-training.js.org"
    • Click "Create pull request"

  4. Wait for approval:

    • Usually takes 1-24 hours
    • Once approved, rivals-training.js.org will point to your site!

Step 5: Update Your GitHub Pages Settings (After Approval)

  1. Go to your repo Settings ‚Üí Pages
  2. Under "Custom domain", enter: rivals-training.js.org
  3. Check "Enforce HTTPS"
  4. Done!

‚ö° FASTER Alternative: Use Netlify Instead

While waiting for js.org approval, you can deploy to Netlify NOW:

  2. Drag your folder

  4. Later, you can still add rivals-training.js.org as a custom domain
